---
import PageHeader from "../components/PageHeader.astro";
import SiteLayout from "../components/SiteLayout.astro";
import { site } from "../data/site";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="About"
  description="Profile page for Tayyub Yaqoob covering role, focus, training, and the operating principles behind the work."
  pathname="/about"
  crumbs={[{ label: "Home", href: "/" }, { label: "About" }]}
  pageType="about"
>
  <style slot="head">
    .creds{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:10px;margin-top:24px}
    .cred{background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:var(--r-md);padding:14px 16px;display:flex;gap:12px;align-items:flex-start;transition:transform .25s,border-color .25s,box-shadow .25s}
    .cred:hover{transform:translateY(-2px);border-color:var(--line-2);box-shadow:var(--shadow-1)}
    .cred-issuer{width:38px;height:38px;border-radius:9px;flex-shrink:0;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-family:var(--sans);font-weight:800;font-size:14px;letter-spacing:-.02em;color:#fff}
    .cred-issuer.google{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4285f4,#34a853 33%,#fbbc05 66%,#ea4335)}
    .cred-issuer.linkedin{background:#0a66c2}
    .cred-issuer.aws{background:#ff9900;color:#1a1714}
    .cred-body{flex:1;min-width:0}
    .cred-body h5{font-family:var(--sans);font-weight:600;font-size:13.5px;line-height:1.3;color:var(--ink);letter-spacing:-.005em;margin-bottom:3px}
    .cred-body .cred-meta{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.04em;color:var(--muted);text-transform:uppercase}
    .cred-body .cred-skills{display:flex;gap:5px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:6px}
    .cred-body .cred-skills span{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.04em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:2px 7px;border-radius:999px;background:var(--bg-soft);color:var(--ink-2);border:1px solid var(--line)}
    @media (max-width:680px){.creds{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
  </style>

  <PageHeader
    title="About the <em>work</em>."
    subtitle="The core thesis of this site is simple: <b>AI systems and analytics engineering leader</b>. Everything else on the site — publications, peer review, public code, and press context — supports that reading rather than competing with it."
    crumbs={[{ label: "Home", href: "/" }, { label: "About" }]}
  />

  <section class="section wrap first" data-screen-label="Bio">
    <div class="about">
      <div class="about-card rv">
        <div class="about-photo"><img src={site.image} alt={site.name} /></div>
        <div class="about-id">
          <div class="name">{site.name}</div>
          <div class="role">{site.role}</div>
          <div class="meta">
            <span>Discipline · <b>Digital analytics, AI systems, measurement engineering</b></span>
            <span>Based · <b>{site.location}</b></span>
            <span>Education · <b>MSc Computing Science, University of Stirling</b></span>
            <span>Status · <b>Open · 2026</b></span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="about-text rv d1">
        <h3>I build <em>analytics systems</em> that people can rely on.</h3>
        <p>My work sits at the intersection of <b>AI / machine learning</b>, <b>data workflows</b>, and <b>digital measurement</b>. The strongest part of the story is not a personal brand line. It is the combination of shipped internal systems, public technical writing, supporting recognition, and evidence that can be examined without exaggeration.</p>
        <p>The site is intentionally structured around <b>case studies</b>, <b>publications</b>, <b>recognition</b>, and <b>evidence</b> because that is how serious reviewers evaluate technical credibility. I would rather make the proof path obvious than make the copy sound grand.</p>
        <p>Current areas of focus include <b>AI-assisted analytics workflows</b>, <b>measurement QA automation</b>, <b>consent and reporting transparency</b>, and <b>AI-search visibility research</b>.</p>

        <h4 style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10.5px;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--terra);margin:32px 0 12px">§ Training and credentials</h4>

        <div class="creds">
          <div class="cred"><div class="cred-issuer google">G</div><div class="cred-body"><h5>5-Day AI Agents Intensive Course</h5><div class="cred-meta">Google · Dec 2025</div><div class="cred-skills"><span>AI Agents</span><span>Python</span></div></div></div>
          <div class="cred"><div class="cred-issuer linkedin">in</div><div class="cred-body"><h5>Vertex AI: MLOps with Google Cloud</h5><div class="cred-meta">LinkedIn · Jun 2025</div><div class="cred-skills"><span>Vertex AI</span><span>MLOps</span></div></div></div>
          <div class="cred"><div class="cred-issuer linkedin">in</div><div class="cred-body"><h5>Model Context Protocol — Hands-On with Agentic AI</h5><div class="cred-meta">LinkedIn · Jun 2025</div><div class="cred-skills"><span>MCP</span><span>AI Agents</span></div></div></div>
          <div class="cred"><div class="cred-issuer aws">AWS</div><div class="cred-body"><h5>AWS Certified Machine Learning — Specialty Prep</h5><div class="cred-meta">LinkedIn · Jun 2025</div><div class="cred-skills"><span>Machine Learning</span><span>AWS</span></div></div></div>
          <div class="cred"><div class="cred-issuer linkedin">in</div><div class="cred-body"><h5>Agentic AI for Developers</h5><div class="cred-meta">LinkedIn · Jun 2025</div><div class="cred-skills"><span>AI Agents</span><span>Enterprise AI</span></div></div></div>
          <div class="cred"><div class="cred-issuer linkedin">in</div><div class="cred-body"><h5>Generative AI with OpenAI API for Production</h5><div class="cred-meta">LinkedIn · Jun 2025</div><div class="cred-skills"><span>OpenAI API</span><span>Generative AI</span></div></div></div>
        </div>

        <div class="principles" style="margin-top:36px">
          <div class="principle"><span class="num">/ 01</span><h4>Evidence before claims.</h4><p>If a statement cannot point to a live URL, approved output, archive asset, or recommendation context, it should be softened or removed.</p></div>
          <div class="principle"><span class="num">/ 02</span><h4>Systems over slogans.</h4><p>Shipped workflows, useful tooling, and repeatable measurement matter more than polished adjectives.</p></div>
          <div class="principle"><span class="num">/ 03</span><h4>Public proof is rarely the whole proof.</h4><p>Confidential work still matters, but it has to be surfaced honestly through safe artefacts and context.</p></div>
          <div class="principle"><span class="num">/ 04</span><h4>Recognition supports the work; it does not replace it.</h4><p>Publications, peer review, and citations are useful signals, but the core case stays operational and technical.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
